{
  "name": "Leaf Uppercut",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Taijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You perform a single backflip kick or rising uppercut with enough force to crack the ground underneath you. Make a single melee taijutsu attack. On a hit, you knock the creature 30 feet into the air dealing 3d6 bludgeoning damage.</p><p>Until the end of your turn, you can target one affected creature with a Taijutsu Finisher regardless of range, once per turn, using either an Action or Bonus action, ignoring its listed casting time. If the Taijutsu Finisher has the Leaf prefix, it increases its damage by +1 damage die.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 1d6.</p>",
